Tool Call: retrieve("recent studies on multi-modal cervical physical therapy for cervicogenic somatic tinnitus")

Retrieved Documents: 32 documents

\boxed{C}
I reviewed the retrieved evidence, which confirms the established physiological connection between cervical dysfunction and tinnitus through somatosensory pathways involving the dorsal cochlear nucleus. However, none of the sources report direct clinical trials or outcome data assessing the effectiveness of multi-modal cervical physical therapy specifically for reducing tinnitus severity in cervicogenic cases. While some materials mention stress reduction and cognitive therapies as part of tinnitus management, they do not support claims about improved tinnitus due to physical therapy modalities targeting cervical structures. Therefore, I maintain my original position that there is insufficient evidence to confirm benefit. \boxed{C}
